52.7	Howard_Shore	Howard Shore	Howard Leslie Shore (born October 18, 1946) is a Canadian composer, notable for his film scores. He has composed the scores for over 80 films, most notably the scores for The Lord of the Rings film trilogy, for which he won three Academy Awards. He is also a consistent collaborator with director David Cronenberg, having scored all but one of his films since 1979.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d6/Howard_Shore_in_2010.jpg/220px-Howard_Shore_in_2010.jpg
